{% call band.output("Usage") -%}
  <p>
    A Call to action is used to entice users to select a link or display hidden content, depending on the style. For example, use the Primary style to bring attention to an important link or use the Brick style to organize links in a grid that also display hidden content.
  </p>

  <h3>Navigation vs. action</h3>

  <p>
    Use Calls to action only as navigational elements and use <a href="#">Buttons</a> <!-- future link --> to perform actions.
  </p>

  <h3>Labels</h3>

  <p>
    Call to action labels are written differently than Button labels. Call to action labels should be more creative or expressive to better entice users to make a selection.
  </p>

  <h3>Hierarchy</h3>
  <p>Calls to action are ordered by hierarchy from left to right or sometimes <a href="#">top to bottom</a> (<!-- future link to responsive design content -->. Similar styles can be used multiple times in the same area except for the Primary and Primary, disabled styles.</p>

