{% call band.output("Behavior") -%}
<h3>Call to action vs. Button</h3>
<p>A Call to action directs users to other pages or sometimes displays hidden content whereas a Button performs an action. For example, a Button shouldn’t be used as a link and a Call to action shouldn’t be used to submit a form. Calls to action and Buttons can be used in the same area as long as the styles are used properly and perform the right functions.</p>

<h3>Bricks</h3>
<p>Sometimes the Brick styles can act like <a href="#">Accordions</a> <!--future link --> where they slide vertically to reveal hidden content when selected. Otherwise, they act like a list of links that are grouped together in a grid.</p>

<img src="/assets/cta/cta-brick-list.png"><img src="/assets/cta/cta-brick-accordion.png">

<h3>Responsive design</h3>
<p>Calls to action maintain the same scale on desktop and mobile. If they stack, the alignment and the order of hierarchy stays the same, which is left to right and top to bottom. If a Call to action contains a background or a border, the label stays centered if it’s really long and if it breaks to two lines.</p>
{%- endcall %}

